'''Jayne Mansfield's leopard spot bikini''' was regular wardrobe for actress and [[Bombshell (sex symbol)|blonde bombshell]] [[Jayne Mansfield]] in her publicity stunts.<ref>{{cite news |author=Staff Correspondent |title=The bare facts at last, all those hours at the gym will pay off with spring's slightly skimpy fashions |newspaper=Miami Herald |page=D1 |date=March 12, 1986 }}</ref><ref>{{cite news |author=Kilgallen, Dorothy |title=Jayne's Touring Strawhats in Bikinis |newspaper=The Washington Post |page=B11 |date=July 22, 1964 }}</ref> Because of the costume she came to be known as "the girl in the leopard bikini" at times.<ref>Kelly Killoren Bensimon, ''The bikini book'', page 45, Thames & Hudson, 2006, {{ISBN|9780500513163}}</ref> Throughout the 1950s, she and her husband [[Mickey Hargitay]] posed for photos with her in the leopard spot bikini.<ref>Jane Woolridge, "[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=8GxJAAAAIBAJ&sjid=pQoNAAAAIBAJ&pg=5231,615022&dq=jayne+mansfield+leopard+spot+bikini&hl=en Bare it and grin this spring]", ''[[The News and Courier]]'', page 3, 1986-04-03</ref> The couple wore matching leopard spots to announce their closeness,<ref>{{harvnb|Saxton|1975|p=94}}</ref> and the costume won them a prize at a Hollywood costume party.<ref>"[https://books.google.com/books?id=vkEEAAAAMBAJ&pg=PA59&dq=jayne+mansfield+leopard+spot+bikini&hl=en&sa=X&ei=7gDJT6icCcPsrAeEu_XLDg&ved=0CGEQ6AEwBQ#v=onepage&q&f=false Muscular hoist for Jayne]", ''[[Life (magazine)|Life]]'', page 59, 1956-11-12</ref> Mansfield often walked down the [[Hollywood Boulevard]] in the leopard bikini signing autographs,<ref>John Waters, ''Crackpot: The Obsessions of John Waters'', page 113, Simon and Schuster, 2003, {{ISBN|9780743246279}}</ref> once went shopping in the leopard bikini,<ref>{{Harvnb|Strait|1992|pp=74–76}}</ref> and attended parties in it.<ref>"[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=iDgeAAAAIBAJ&sjid=k8sEAAAAIBAJ&pg=6500,4093663&dq=jayne+mansfield+leopard+bikini&hl=en Bikini clad Jayne Mansfield carried to party by friend]", ''[[Daytona Beach Morning Journal]]'', page 7, 1956-10-29</ref><ref>"[https://news.google.com/newspapers?id=k2osAAAAIBAJ&sjid=bcsEAAAAIBAJ&pg=5526,4142645&dq=jayne+mansfield+leopard+bikini&hl=en Ballyhoo Ball wildest one yet in Hollywood]", ''[[Spartanburg Herald-Journal|Herald-Journal]]'', page 3, 1956-10-28</ref>
When Mansfield and her husband [[Miklós Hargitay]] toured for stage shows, newspapers wrote that Mansfield convinced the rural population that she owned more bikinis than anyone.<ref>Dorothy Kilgallen, "Jayne's Touring Strawhats in Bikinis", Washington Post, page B11, 1964-07-22</ref> She showed a fair amount of her {{convert|40|in|mm|adj=on}} bust, as well as her midriff and legs, in the leopard-spot bikini she wore for her stage shows.<ref>Staff Correspondent, "The bare facts at last, all those hours at the gym will pay off with spring's slightly skimpy fashions", ''Miami Herald'', page D1, 1986-03-12</ref> Kathryn Wexler of ''[[The Miami Herald]]'' wrote, "In the beginning as we know it, there was Jayne Mansfield. Here she preens in leopard-print or striped bikinis, sucking in air to showcase her well noted physical assets."<ref>Kathryn Wexler, "[http://www.accessmylibrary.com/coms2/summary_0286-14911424_ITM Old-time eroticism: When bikinis really mattered]", ''Miami Herald'', 2006-04-19</ref> Her [[Leopard (pattern)|leopard-skin]] bikini remains one of the earlier specimens of the fashion.<ref>[[Jennifer Steinhauer]], "[https://query.nytimes.com/gst/fullpage.html?res=9D0DE0D91539F932A25756C0A961958260 In, Damned Spot!], [[New York Times]], 1997-05-11</ref> As late as in 1982, she appeared in a full page color photograph in the leopard spot bikini in Tony Crawley's ''Screen Dreams: The Hollywood Pin-up''.<ref>{{harvnb|Faris|1994|p=159}}</ref> ''American Photo'' magazine printed photographer Bruno Bernard's photo of Mansfield in the costume in 2003.<ref>"[https://books.google.com/books?id=Ujno8pBBTHsC&pg=PA13&dq=jayne+mansfield+leopard+bikini&hl=en&sa=X&ei=jQbJT4fQKrHImAXE4-jyDg&ved=0CF4Q6AEwBQ#v=onepage&q=leopard%20&f=false Inside Photography]", ''American Photo'', page 13, Jan-Feb 2003</ref>
