[[File:Károly Marót (1885-1963) teacher of Classical philology.jpg|thumbnail|right|Károly Marót]] '''Károly Marót''' (Arad, 2 March 1885 - Budapest, 27 October 1963), was a Hungarian classical scholar,<ref name=Rtt>Rttook, Zsigmund. (1997) [http://epa.niif.hu/01400/01462/00020/pdf/005-015.pdf "The contribution of Hungary to international classical scholarship"], ''[[Hungarian Studies (journal)|Hungarian Studies]]'', 12. Retrieved 7 March 2014. [https://www.webcitation.org/6NtepxQmg?url=http://epa.niif.hu/01400/01462/00020/pdf/005-015.pdf Archived here.]</ref> [[philologist]] and member of the [[Hungarian Academy of Sciences]].
Marót specialised in the study of [[Epic poetry|ancient epic]], particularly the works of [[Homer]], and interpreted the works using the latest ideas in psychiatry about the [[subconscious]].<ref name=Rtt/>
==Selected publications== *''Der eid als tat''. Szegred, Szeged Városi Nyomda és Könyvkiadó, 1924. *''A Görög irodalom kezdetei''. Budapest, Akadémiai Kiadó, 1956. *''Die anfänge der Griechischen litteratur vorfragen''. 1960.
