{{Muisca sidebar}} This list contains '''Muisca and pre-Muisca scholars'''; researchers, historians, archaeologists, anthropologists and other investigators who have contributed to the current knowledge of the [[Muisca people|Muisca]] and their ancestors of the [[Muisca Confederation#Prehistory|prehistory of the Altiplano Cundiboyacense]] and of the [[Andean preceramic|preceramic]] and ceramic [[Herrera Period]]s.
Other than the [[Mesoamerica]]nists and scholars of the [[Inca Empire|Incas]], Muisca scholars are not too abundant. Most of the early Muisca knowledge comes from the Spanish conquistadores and missionaries working in the Americas. __NOTOC__
