== 2017 – Trump administration == {{further|Timeline of the presidency of Donald Trump}}
=== January === * '''January''': ** For two days in early January 2017, in a gathering [[George Nader (businessman)|George Nader]] attended and brokered, [[Joel Zamel]] and General [[Ahmad Asiri (general)|Ahmed Al-Assiri]] met with [[Michael Flynn]] and other members of the Trump transition team in New York. [[Steve Bannon]] was involved as well. In October 2018, the meeting came under the Mueller investigation's scrutiny.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/saudi-spy-met-with-team-trump-about-taking-down-iran |title=Saudi Spy Met With Team Trump About Taking Down Iran: Mueller’s investigators examined a series of meetings between an Israeli social media strategist, the general blamed for Jamal Khashoggi’s murder, and Trump adviser Michael Flynn. |authors=Betsy Woodruff and Erin Banco |date=25 October 2018 |website=Thedailybeast.com |publisher= |access-date=25 October 2018 |quote=}}</ref> ** [[White House Counsel]] [[Donald McGahn]] tells Trump he believes that Flynn had misled the FBI and lied to Vice President Pence, and should be fired.<ref>{{Cite news |url=http://www.cnn.com/2017/12/04/politics/wh-lawyer-told-trump-flynn-misled-fbi-pence/index.html |title=WH lawyer told Trump that Flynn misled FBI, VP |last=Scannell |first=Kara |work=CNN|access-date=December 4, 2017}}</ref> ** McGahn researches the [[Logan Act]] and federal laws related to lying to federal investigators. Records turned over to the Mueller investigation show McGahn believes Flynn violated one or more of those laws.<ref name=McGahnKnewFlynnBrokeLawFP20171220 />[[File:Rice email 180212.pdf|thumb|Susan Rice's email to herself on January 20, 2017.]] * '''January 20''': ** Trump and Pence [[inauguration of Donald Trump|take office]].<ref>{{cite news |url= http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/melania-trump-channels-jacqueline-kennedy-onassis-inaugural-day/story?id=44914681 |title=Melania Trump Channels Jacqueline Kennedy Onassis in Inaugural Day Fashion |work=[[ABC News]] |first=Katie |last=Kindelan |date=January 20, 2017 |access-date=May 25, 2017}}</ref> ** While seated at Trump's [[Inauguration of Donald Trump#Inaugural address|inauguration speech]], Flynn texts Alex Copson, chairman of ACU Strategic Partners, that Russian sanctions blocking a private Russian-backed plan to build nuclear plants in the Middle East will now be "ripped up".<ref>{{cite news |url=https://finance.yahoo.com/news/whistleblower-inauguration-flynn-texted-nuclear-180906476.html |title=Whistleblower: Flynn texts broached nuclear plan, sanctions |work=Yahoo News |date=December 6, 2017|agency=Associated Press|last=Braun|first=Stephen}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=http://www.denverpost.com/2017/12/06/michael-flynn-russia-sanctions-donald-trump/ |title=Witness: Flynn said Russia sanctions would be "ripped up" |work=Denver Post |date=December 6, 2017|last=Hamburger|first=Tom|agency=The Washington Post}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2017/dec/06/michael-flynn-russia-sanctions-trump-inauguration |title=Flynn texted during inauguration to suggest Russia sanctions would end, Democrat says |work=The Guardian |date=December 6, 2017|agency=Associated Press}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-42260087 |title=Flynn said Russia sanctions would be 'ripped up' – congressman |work=BBC |date=December 6, 2017}}</ref><ref name=FlynnRippedUpSanctionsNYT20171206 /> An associate of Copson later denies the allegation.<ref name="reuters-20171211">{{cite news |url=https://uk.reuters.com/article/uk-usa-trump-russia-flynn/nuclear-plan-backer-denies-inauguration-day-text-with-top-trump-aide-idUKKBN1E52IS |title=Nuclear plan backer denies Inauguration Day text with top Trump aide |work=[[Reuters]] |date=December 11, 2017|author=Reuters Staff}}</ref> ** Sergei Millian, Source D in the [[Steele dossier]], attends VIP inauguration events.<ref>{{cite web |title=Who is ‘Source D’? The man said to be behind the Trump-Russia dossier’s most salacious claim. |url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/who-is-source-d-the-man-said-to-be-behind-the-trump-russia-dossiers-most-salacious-claim/2017/03/29/379846a8-0f53-11e7-9d5a-a83e627dc120_story.html |work=[[The Washington Post]] |date=March 29, 2018|access-date=March 16, 2018 |last1=Helderman |first1=Rosalind S. |last2=Hamburger |first2=Ton}}</ref> ** [[Natalia Veselnitskaya]], the Russian lawyer involved in the June 2016 Trump Tower meeting, and [[Rinat Akhmetshin]], another participant in that meeting, attend the [[Inauguration of Donald Trump#Inaugural balls|Liberty Ball]]<ref name=FromRussiaToBistroBiABCNews20180726 /> at the [[Library of Congress]] hosted by Representative [[Dana Rohrabacher]]'s campaign committee. Akhmetshin later claims he received tickets from event organizers, but Rohrabacher's office claims the campaign has no record of such an invitation or of ticket purchases by the two.<ref name=RussiansAtInaugurationWapo20190120>{{cite news |title=In the crowd at Trump’s inauguration, members of Russia’s elite anticipated a thaw between Moscow and Washington |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/amid-trumps-inaugural-festivities-members-of-russias-elite-anticipated-a-thaw-between-moscow-and-washington/2018/01/20/0d767f46-fb9f-11e7-ad8c-ecbb62019393_story.html |work=[[The Washington Post]] |date=January 20, 2018|access-date=March 17, 2018 |last1=Timberg |first1=Craig |last2=Helderman |first2=Rosalind S. |last3=Roth |first3=Andrew |last4=Leonnig |first4=Carol D.}}</ref> Ticket sales are counted as donations [[United States House of Representatives elections in California, 2018|to Rohrabacher's campaign]]. In July 2018, Rohrabacher spokesman Kenneth Grubbs tells ABC News, "Apparently, there was some party-crashing going on."<ref name=FromRussiaToBistroBiABCNews20180726>{{cite web|title=From Russia to Bistro Bis: The Calif. congressman who dined with alleged Russian agent|url=https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/russia-bistro-bis-calif-congressman-dined-a