ntencePolitico20180817 /><ref name=PapadopoulosSentencingMemorandum20180817 /> In October 2017 he will plead guilty to making omissions and false statements during the interview.<ref name=TrumpCampaignAdviserLiedHuffpo20171030>{{cite news |title=Trump Campaign Adviser Lied To FBI About Russian 'Dirt' |url=http://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/entry/george-papadopolous-trump-russia-probe_us_59f7354be4b07fdc5fbfa210 |work=HuffPost |date=October 30, 2017|last=Reilly|first=Ryan J.}}</ref><ref name=PapadopoulosStatementOfOffense>{{cite news|url= https://static01.nyt.com/packages/pdf/politics/2017/statement_of_the_offense.filed_.pdf|title=USA v Papadopoulos – Statement of the Offense|publisher=[[The New York Times Company]]|format=[[PDF]]}}</ref> Hours after the interview, he applies for the position of Deputy Assistant Secretary in the [[United States Department of Energy|Department of Energy]].<ref name=MuellerRecommendsSentencePolitico20180817>{{cite web|title=Mueller recommends sentence up to 6 months for Papadopoulos|url=https://www.politico.com/story/2018/08/17/papadopoulous-mueller-sentencing-trump-campaign-russia-787835|website=[[Politico]]|date=August 17, 2018|access-date=August 17, 2018|last1=Forgey|first1=Quint|last2=Cheney|first2=Kyle}}</ref><ref name=PapadopoulosSentencingMemorandum20180817>{{cite web|title=United States v. George Papadopoulos, Government's Sentencing Memorandum|url=https://www.politico.com/f/?id=00000165-4ab8-d0d5-af75-fbfc1ad30001|format=PDF|date=August 17, 2018|access-date=August 17, 2018|last1=Mueller III|first1=Robert S.|last2=Rhee|first2=Jeannie S.|last3=Goldstein|first3=Andrew D.|last4=Zelinsky|first4=Aaron S.J.|via=[[Politico]]|author-link1=Robert Mueller|author-link2=Jeannie Rhee|author-link3=Andrew D. Goldstein}}</ref> ** McGahn has further discussions with Yates about Flynn.<ref name="beggin8may">{{cite news |last1=Beggin |first1=Riley |last2=Stracqualursi |first2=Veronica |title=A timeline of Yates' warnings to the White House about Mike Flynn |url= http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/timeline-sally-yates-warnings-white-house-mike-flynn/story?id=47272979 |accessdate=May 29, 2017 |publisher=[[ABC News]] |date=May 8, 2017}}</ref> ** During a private dinner at the White House, Comey gets the impression that Trump wants to "create some sort of patronage relationship." Comey will later testify that Trump requested "loyalty" from him, and that he offered "honesty" instead.<ref name="schmidt11may">{{cite news |last1=Schmidt |first1=Michael S. |authorlink=Michael S. Schmidt|title=In a Private Dinner, Trump Demanded Loyalty. Comey Demurred. |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/05/11/us/politics/trump-comey-firing.html |accessdate=May 29, 2017 |work=[[The New York Times]] |date=May 11, 2017}}</ref> ** Deripaska's longtime American lobbyist Adam Waldman visits Julian Assange.<ref name=USLobbyistForRussianGuardian20180620>{{cite web|title=US lobbyist for Russian oligarch visited Julian Assange nine times last year|url=https://www.theguardian.com/media/2018/jun/20/us-lobbyist-for-russian-oligarch-visited-julian-assange-nine-times-last-year|website=[[The Guardian]]|date=June 20, 2018|access-date=August 20, 2018|last1=Kirchgaessner|first1=Stehanie|last2=Harding|first2=Luke|author-link2=Luke Harding}}</ref> * '''January 29''': Trump's lawyers give Mueller a confidential memo and claim that Trump knew only that Flynn had been interviewed by the FBI, and believed Flynn had been cleared.<ref name=ConfidentialMemotoMueller20180602>{{cite web|title=The Trump Lawyers’ Confidential Memo to Mueller, Explained|url=https://www.nytimes.com/interactive/2018/06/02/us/politics/trump-legal-documents.html|website=[[The New York Times]]|date=June 2, 2018|access-date=June 2, 2018}}</ref><ref name=Waas2018/> * '''January 31''': ** Trump [[Sally Yates#Dismissal|dismisses Yates]] for refusing to enforce [[Executive Order 13769]], calling it "betrayal" and "weak".<ref>{{cite news |last=Gerstein |first=Josh |title=Trump fires defiant acting at