=== February === * '''February''': ** According to later reporting by [[Michael Wolff (journalist)|Michael Wolff]], former British Prime Minister [[Tony Blair]], during a visit to the White House, warns Kushner that UK intelligence services may have had the Trump campaign under surveillance. Blair denies Wolff's claims.<ref>{{cite news |url= https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/2018/01/03/tony-blair-warned-trump-aides-britain-may-have-spied-election/ |title=Tony Blair warned Trump aides Britain may have spied on them during election, new book claims |work=[[The Daily Telegraph]] |date=January 3, 2018|last=Riley-Smith|first=Ben}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2018/jan/04/tony-blair-donald-trump-gchq-spied |title=Tony Blair ‘warned Donald Trump UK may have spied on him’ |work=[[The Guardian]] |date=January 4, 2017|last1=Weaver|first1=Matthew|last2=Slawson|first2=Nicola}}</ref> ** Paul Manafort and Rick Gates falsely assert for a second time in writing to the Justice Department that their work for the Ukrainian government did not require [[Foreign Agents Registration Act|registering as foreign agents]] in the United States. In September 2018, Manafort pleads guilty to lying to the Justice Department about the extent of his work for the Ukrainian government.<ref>{{cite web|title=[[commons:File:Paul Manafort statement of the offense and other acts 17-201-01(ABJ)).pdf|United States of America v. Paul Manafort, Jr. – Statement of the offense and other acts]]|date=September 14, 2018|access-date=September 14, 2018|format=PDF|last1=Mueller III|first1=Robert S.|author-link1=Robert Mueller|last2=Weissmann|first2=Andrew|last3=Rhee|first3=Jeanie S.|last4=Andres|first4=Greg D.|last5=Freeny|first5=Kyle R.|author-link2=Andrew Weissmann|via=[[Wikimedia Commons]]}}</ref> * '''Early February''': Cohen delivers a pro-Russian Ukrainian peace plan to Flynn while visiting the White House. The plan was developed by Sater and [[Andrii Artemenko]], a Ukrainian politician who said he was encouraged by "top aides" to Putin.<ref name="twohey19february">{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/02/19/us/politics/donald-trump-ukraine-russia.html |title=A Back-Channel Plan for Ukraine and Russia, Courtesy of Trump Associates |date=February 19, 2017 |work=[[The New York Times]] |last2=Shane |first2=Scott |last1=Twohey |first1=Megan |author-link1=Megan Twohey|authorlink2=Scott Shane|accessdate=May 29, 2017}}</ref> The meeting was arranged by Ukrainian-American Alex Oronov, whose daughter is married to Cohen's brother.<ref name=OronovDiesIndependent20170306>{{cite news|title=Ukranian<!--sic--> businessman with links to Donald Trump and Russia dies in unexplained circumstances|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/americas/ukranian-businesman-russia-and-donald-trump-dies-michael-cohen-michael-flynn-donald-trump-vladimir-a7612866.html|work=[[The Independent]]|date=March 6, 2017|access-date=March 18, 2018|last=Roberts|first=Rachel}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=A Suspicious Death In Trump's Orbit? "Total Bullshit," Says Family|url=https://www.buzzfeed.com/jasonaleopold/a-suspicious-death-in-trumps-orbit-total-bullshit-says-famil|work=[[BuzzFeed News]]|date=March 6, 2017|access-date=March 18, 2018|last1=Leopold|first1=Jason| last2=McDaniel| first2=Chris|last3=Cormier|first3=Anthony}}</ref> Allen Tactical Security Consultants founder Tommy Allen vetted the peace plan at the request of former congressman [[Curt Weldon]], a longtime friend of Artemenko.<ref name=SenateInvestigatorsMayHaveAtlantic20180607>{{cite web|title=Senate Investigators May Have Found a Missing Piece in the Russia Probe|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2018/06/former-gop-congressman-embroiled-in-the-russia-probe/562343/|website=[[The Atlantic]]|date=June 7, 2018|access-date=September 4, 2018|last=Bertrand|first=Natasha}}</ref> Artemenko and Weldon secured funding for promoting the plan from Vekselberg's fund at [[Columbus Nova]].<ref name=Sena