ueller20180602/> * '''February 9''': ** ''The Washington Post'' reports that Flynn privately discussed Russian sanctions with Kislyak before Trump took office, which Flynn had previously denied. Flynn's spokesman now says, "[Flynn] couldn’t be certain that the topic never came up.”<ref name=FlynnKislyakWapo20170209 /> ** Representative [[Jerrold Nadler]] (D-NY) introduces a [[resolution of inquiry]] in relation to possible crimes relating to Trump's financial dealings or collusion with Russia.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.countable.us/articles/237-preliminary-impeachment-inquiry-filed-president-trump |title=Preliminary Impeachment Inquiry Filed Against President Trump |website=[[Countable.us]] |date=February 9, 2017 |access-date=May 27, 2017}}</ref> * '''February 10''' ** Trump tells reporters he did not know about Flynn's December discussions of sanctions with Kislyak.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.cnn.com/2017/02/10/politics/flynn-russia-us-sanctions-reports/|title=Trump says he's unaware of reports Flynn discussed sanctions with Russian ambassador|website=[[CNN]]|date=February 10, 2017|access-date=March 18, 2018|last1=Liptak|first1=Kevin|last2=Zeleny|first2=Jeff|last3=Landers|first3=Elizabeth}}</ref> ** According to Trump's lawyers, Flynn tells McGahn, Priebus, and Pence in a phone call that the FBI had said their investigation was being "closed out."<ref name=ConfidentialMemotoMueller20180602 /> * '''February 11''': Flynn omits his paid trip to the [[Russia Today]] 10th anniversary gala on a financial disclosure form.<ref name=FlynnOmitsRTSpeechDailyBeast20180401>{{cite news|title=Michael Flynn Failed to Disclose Payments From Russian Propaganda Network|url=https://www.thedailybeast.com/michael-flynn-failed-to-disclose-payments-from-russian-propaganda-network|website=[[The Daily Beast]]|date=April 1, 2017|access-date=March 27, 2018|last=Markay|first=Lachlan}}</ref> * '''February 13''': ** Flynn is dismissed after less than a month in office.<ref>{{cite web |