om/23cca28e11b74f0cb369fda6fac64d67/white-house-staff-told-preserve-russia-related-materials|website=[[Associated Press]]|date=March 2, 2017|access-date=March 18, 2018|last1=Pace|first1=Julie|last2=Salama|first2=Vivian}}</ref> ** Aleksej Gubarev files a libel suit against ''BuzzFeed'' in the [[U.S. District Court for the Southern District of Florida]] for publishing the Steele dossier.<ref name=GubrevBuzzFeedRequestForInternationalJudicialAssistance20170810>{{cite web|title=Aleksej Gubarev, XBT Hodings S.A., and Webzilla, Inc. v. BuzzFeed, Inc. and Ben Smith - Request for International Judicial Assistance|url=https://www.politico.com/f/?id=0000015d-ce23-d020-a1df-ce37d9510002|format=PDF|via=[[Politico]]|last=Ungaro|first=Ursula|date=August 10, 2017|access-date=August 21, 2018}}</ref>
=== March === * '''March''' **[[Citigroup]] gives Kushner's company a $325 million loan days after Kushner meets with [[Citigroup]]'s [[CEO]] [[Michael Corbat]].<ref name=KushnerLoansNYT20189228>{{Cite news |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2018/02/28/business/jared-kushner-apollo-citigroup-loans.html |title=Kushner’s Business Got Loans from Companies After White House Meetings |last=Drucker |first=Jesse |date=February 28, 2018 |work=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=March 1, 2018 |last2=Kelly |first2=Kate |language=en-US |issn=0362-4331 |last3=Protess |first3=Ben}}</ref> Kushner also borrows $75 million from [[Apollo Global Management]] and $10 million from Rockwood Capital. In April 2018, lawyers for Apollo tell ''The Guardian'' that the money was used by Kushner to buy out real estate positions owned by Invesco Real Estate. The lawyers insist Kushner and Apollo CEO [[Joshua Harris (businessman)|Joshua Harris]] did not discuss Apollo's loan before it was granted.<ref>{{cite web|title=Wall St star approached to be Trump budget chief a year before loan to Kushner firm |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2018/apr/08/jared-kushner-joshua-harris-budget-director-loan-trump|website=[[The Guardian]]|last=Kirchgaessner|first=Stephanie|date=April 9, 2018|access-date=August 20, 2018}}</ref> ** Based upon a complaint by Senators [[Patrick Leahy]] and [[Al Frankin|Al Franken]], the FBI opens an investigation into whether Sessions [[perjured]] himself during testimony before the [[Senate Judiciary Committee]].<ref>{{cite web|title=EXCLUSIVE: Fired FBI official authorized criminal probe of Sessions, sources say|url=https://abcnews.go.com/US/exclusive-fired-fbi-official-authorized-criminal-probe-sessions/story?id=53914006|date=March 21, 2018|access-date=June 27, 2018|last=Levine|first=Mike}}</ref> * '''March 1''': ** Sessions comes under scrutiny after reports that he had contact with Russian government officials during the election campaign, even though he denied it during his confirmation hearings. Democratic representatives ask Sessions to resign his post as United States Attorney General.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.usatoday.com/story/news/politics/2017/03/02/attorney-general-jeff-sessions-perjury-confirmation-hearing-russia/98643620/ |title=Did Attorney General Jeff Sessions misspeak, lie — or commit perjury? |last=Wolf |first=Richard |date=March 4, 2017 |publisher=USA Today}}</ref> ** Comey receives an "urgent" call from Trump that Comey views as an attempt to win him over to Trump's side.<ref>{{cite news|title=Comey, Unsettled by Trump, Is Said to Have Wanted Him Kept at a Distance|url= https://www.nytimes.com/2017/05/18/us/politics/james-comey-memo-fbi-trump.html|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=May 18, 2017|access-date=March 18, 2018|last=Schmidt|first=Michael S.|authorlink=Michael S. Schmidt}}</ref> * '''March 1–2''': On Trump's instructions, McGahn attempts to persuade Sessions to stop recusing himself from the Russia investigation.<ref name=nyt-20180104>{{cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2018/01/04/us/politics/trump-sessions-russia-mcgahn.html |title=Obstruction Inquiry Shows Trump’s Struggle to Keep Grip on Russia Investigation |last=Schmidt |first=Michael S. |author-link=Michael S. Schmidt |date=January 4, 2018 |work=[[The New York Times]] |access-date=January 5, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.foxnews.com/politics/2018/01/04/trump-had-white-house-lawyer-urge-sessions-against-russia-recusal-report-says.html |title=Trump had White House lawyer urge Sessions against Russia recusal, report says |date=January 4, 2018 |publisher=Fox News|author1=Fox News|author2=Associated Press}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2018/jan/04/donald-trump-jeff-sessions-russia-inquiry-urge-not-recuse |title=Trump tried to stop Sessions recusing himself from Russia inquiry, sources say |date=January 5, 2018 |publisher=The Guardian|agency=[[Associated Press]]}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.