ped]] [[Trump Tower]], referring to the accusations Trump made via [[Twitter]].<ref>{{cite web|title='Clearly the president is wrong': House intel committee says it's seen 'no evidence' that Obama wiretapped Trump Tower|url=http://www.businessinsider.com/obama-wiretapped-trump-tower-evidence-intelligence-committee-2017-3|website=[[Business Insider]]|date=March 15, 2017|access-date=March 19, 2018|last=Bertrand|first=natasha}}</ref> * '''Late March''': Adam Waldman visits Assange twice.<ref name=USLobbyistForRussianGuardian20180620 /> * '''March 16''': ** The [[Senate Intelligence Committee]] leaders issue a joint statement saying they saw "no indications" that [[Trump Tower]] had been [[Telephone tapping|wiretapped]] by the [[U.S. Government]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Senate Intel: "No indications" of Trump Tower surveillance or wiretapping|url=https://www.cbsnews.com/news/senate-intel-no-indications-trump-tower-was-subject-of-surveillance-wiretapping/|website=[[CBS News]]|date=March 16, 2017|access-date=March 19, 2018|last=He|first=Alan}}</ref> ** The [[American Association of Political Consultants]] gives an "International Consultant of the Year" award to Nigel Farage and [[Leave.EU]] in [[Huntington Beach, California]].<ref>{{cite web|title=AAPC awards Tony Fabrizio as Pollster of the Year|url=http://fabriziolee.com/2017/03/20/pollster-of-the-year/|website=Fabrizio Lee|date=March 17, 2017|access-date=July 12, 2018}}</ref> * '''March 17–25''': While in [[Orange County, California]], Farage and Arron Banks attend GOP gatherings at [[Scott Baugh]]'s invitation. Splitting California into two states is discussed at two of the gatherings. Afterwards, Farage's publicist tells ''The Sunday Times'' a fabricated story about Baugh and Gerry Gunster hiring Farage and Banks to help fundraise in California for a campaign to split the state in two.<ref>{{cite web|title=California split overplayed, says Scott Baugh, former Orange County GOP chairman|url=https://www.ocregister.com/2017/04/01/california-split-overplayed-says-scott-baugh-former-orange-county-gop-chairman/|website=[[Orange County Register]]|date=April 1, 2017|access-date=July 13, 2018|last=Wisckol|first=Martin}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The bad boys of Brexit join fight to break up California|url=https://www.thetimes.co.uk/edition/news/the-bad-boys-of-brexit-joinfight-to-break-up-california-k86ptklw3|website=[[The Sunday Times]]|date=March 26, 2017|access-date=July 12, 2018|last=Shipman|first=March 26.}}</ref> * '''March 19''': Rohrabacher and Farage go fishing off the coast of [[Newport, California]]. Rohrabacher posts a photograph of the two on his Facebook page. In July, he removes the photo from Facebook after a journalist posts it on Twitter.<ref name=DeletedPhotoFarageRohrabacherPoliticalScrapbook20170712>{{cite web|title=The deleted photo of Farage’s fishing trip with Putin’s favourite US politician|url=https://politicalscrapbook.net/2017/07/the-deleted-photo-farages-fishing-trip-with-putins-favourite-us-politician/|website=[[Political Scrapbook]]|date=July 12, 2017|access-date=July 12, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite tweet|number=884840730862256128|user=carolecadwalladr|title=What *is* the story here? New photo of Farage emerges. With "Putin's favourite congressman" & associate of Paul Manafort – @DanaRohrabacher|author=Carole Cadwalladr|author-link=Carole Cadwalladr|date=July 11, 2017|access-date=July 12, 2018}}</ref><ref name=PhotoFarageRohrabacherTweet20170712>{{cite tweet|title=And this pic. The one of Veselnitskaya's main US political contact @DanaRohrabacher & @Nigel_Farage? It *has* been deleted. Why? When?|number=885046054806224896|author=Carole Cadwalladr|author-link=Carole Cadwalladr|date=July 12, 2017|access-date=July 12, 2018|user=carolecadwalladr}}</ref> * '''March 20''': ** The [[House Intelligence Committee]] holds its first public hearing. Comey admits that there is an ongoing FBI investigation into whether there were any links between individuals associated with the Russian government and the Trump campaign and whether they coordinated.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/20/us/politics/fbi-investigation-trump-russia-comey.html |title=F.B.I. Is Investigating Trump’s Russia Ties, Comey Confirms |work=[[The New York Times]] |first=Matt|last=Apuzzo|first2=Matthew|last2=Rosenberg|first3=Emmarie|last3=Huetteman |date=March 20, 2017 |accessdate=November 6, 2017}}</ref> ** [[Devin Nunes]] tells [[David Corn]] of ''[[Mother Jones (magazine)|Mother Jones]]'' that he has never heard of [[Carter Page]] or [[Roger Stone]]. Corn is so surprised by the apparent lie that he immediately tweets about it.<ref>{{cite web| title=Republican Congressman Leading Russia Probe Says He’s Never Heard of Key Figures in the Scandal|url= https://www.motherjones.com/politics/2017/03/devin-nunes-intel-committee-says-never-heard-of-roger-stone-carter-page/|work=[[Mother Jones (magazine)|Mother Jones]]|date=March 20, 2017|access-date=March 20, 2018|last=Corn|first=David}}</ref> In February, the [[White House]] asked Nunes to read and debunk a February 14 ''[[New York Times]]'' article<ref name=CampaignRussiaContactsNYT20170214 /> that mentioned Page and Stone being under investigation.<ref>{{cite web| title= Devin Nunes's Curiously Selective Memory|url=https://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2017/03/doubting-the-congressman-in-charge-of-probing-trumps-russia-ties/520344/|website=[[The Atlantic]]|date=March 2017|access-date=March 20, 2018| last=Friedersdorf|first=Conor}}</ref> On March 3, Nunes discussed the article in an interview with Evan Onstot on [[Fresno, California]], television station [[KSEE]]. He said he would not call the people named in the story to appear before his committee.<ref>{{cite web|title=Devin Nunes: One on One|url=http://www.yourcentralvalley.com/news/devin-nunes-one-on-one/666404701|website=yourcentralvalley.com|date=March 3, 2018|access-date=March 20, 2018|type=video}}</ref> ** WikiLeaks again denies communicating with [[Roger Stone]].<ref>{{cite tweet|title=@kyletblaine WikiLeaks & Assange have repeatedly confirmed that they have never communicated with Stone. Why did CNN not include this fact?|date=March 20, 2017|access-date=March 27, 2018|number=843938212456423425|user=WikiLeaks|author=WikiLeaks|author-link=WikiLeaks}}</ref> * '''March 22''': ** Nunes announces that he discovered the intelligence community "incidentally collected" the communications of some members of Trump's [[presidential transition of Donald Trump|transition team]], potentially including the president himself,<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/powerpost/house-intelligence-chair-says-its-possible-trumps-communications-were-intercepted/2017/03/22/f45e18ba-0f2d-11e7-9b0d-d27c98455440_story.html |title=House Intelligence chair says Trump campaign officials were ensnared in surveillance operations |last=Miller |first=Greg |date=March 22, 2017 |work=Washington Post|access-date=December 6, 2017 |last2=Demirjian |first2=Karoun |language=en-US |issn=0190-8286 |last3=Barrett |first3=Devlin}}</ref> and claims that the information was "widely disseminated". It is later confirmed that he learned this from [[United States National Security Council|Senior Director for National Intelligence]] [[Ezra Cohen-Watnick]] and Assistant [[White House Counsel]] Michael Ellis, formerly counsel to Nunes's committee, during his White House visit on the previous day.<ref name=PreserveIntelligeneceNYT20170301>{{Cite news |url= https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/01/us/politics/obama-trump-russia-election-hacking.html |title=Obama Administration Rushed to Preserve Intelligence of Russian Election Hacking |last2=Goldman |first1=Matthew|last1=Rosenberg|first2=Adam |date=March 1, 2017 |work=[[The New York Times]]|access-date=August 9, 2017 |last3=Schmidt |first3=Michael S. |authorlink3=Michael S. Schmidt|language=en-US |issn=0362-4331}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=2 White House Officials Helped Give Nunes Intelligence Reports|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2017/03/30/us/politics/devin-nunes-intelligence-reports.html|work=[[The New York Times]]|date=March 30, 2017|last1=Rosenberg|first1=Matthew|last2=Haberman|first2=Maggie|last3=Goldman|first3=Adam}}</ref> ** Trump asks Director of National Intelligence [[Dan Coats]] and NSA Director [[Michael S. Rogers|Mike Rogers]] to publicly deny any collusion between the Trump campaign and Russia. Both refuse, saying the requests are inappropriate.<ref>{{cite news |last1=Entous |first1=Adam |last2=Nakashima |first2=Ellen |title=Trump asked intelligence chiefs to push back against FBI collusion probe after Comey revealed its existence |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/trump-asked-intelligence-chiefs-to-push-back-against-fbi-collusion-probe-after-comey-revealed-its-existence/2017/05/22/394933bc-3f10-11e7-9869-bac8b446820a_story.html |accessdate=May 29, 2017 |work=[[The Washington Post]] |date=May 22, 2017}}</ref> Coats later tells staffers that Trump also asked him to get Comey to back off the FBI investigation of Flynn.<ref>{{cite news |title=Top intelligence official told associates Trump asked him if he could intervene with Comey on FBI Russia probe| url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/top-intelligence-official-told-associates-trump-asked-him-if-he-could-intervene-with-comey-to-get-fbi-to-back-off-flynn/2017/06/06/cc879f14-4ace-11e7-9669-250d0b15f83b_story.html | work=[[The Washington Post]]|date=June 6, 2017|access-date=March 27, 2018|last=Entous|first=Adam}}</ref> * '''March 23''': [[Rick Gates (political consultant)|Rick Gates]], longtime deputy to Manafort and Trump campaign advisor, is forced to leave the pro-Trump nonprofit [[America First Policies]] after reports that Manafort sought to further Russian interests.<ref name="landers23march">{{cite news |last1=Landers |first1=Elizabeth |last2=Diamond |first2=Jeremy |title=Gates out at nonprofit over Manafort-Russia ties |url=http://www.cnn.