ory.html |title=Rep. Brad Sherman knows Trump won't be impeached any time soon, but he's trying anyway |work=[[LA Times]] |first=Christine |last=Mai-Duc |date=June 12, 2017 |access-date=June 18, 2017}}</ref> * '''June 13''': ** The U.S. Senate agrees on a new package of [[Economic sanctions|sanctions]] on Russia in retaliation to the election interference. The bill is drafted to prevent Trump from lifting sanctions unilaterally.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/wireStory/senate-gop-dems-agree-sanctions-russia-47997685 |title=Senate GOP, Dems agree on new sanctions on Russia |publisher=[[ABC News]] |agency=[[Associated Press]] |first=Richard |last=Lardner |date=June 13, 2017 |access-date=June 13, 2017 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20170613053011/http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/wireStory/senate-gop-dems-agree-sanctions-russia-47997685 |archivedate=June 13, 2017 |df=mdy-all}}</ref> ** Sessions testifies before the Senate Intelligence Committee.<ref>{{cite news |work=[[The Washington Post]] |url= https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/jeff-sessions-set-to-testify-this-afternoon-before-senate-intelligence-committee/2017/06/13/ac5321bc-4fc6-11e7-91eb-9611861a988f_story.html |title=Jeff Sessions testifies: Refuses to say whether he spoke to Trump about Comey’s handling of Russia investigation |date=June 13, 2017|last1=Horwitz|first1=Sari|last2=Barrett|first2=Devlin|last3=Zapotosky|first3=Matt}}</ref> ** Rosenstein testifies to the Senate that he is the only person empowered to dismiss Mueller, and that he sees no reason to do so.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2017-06-13/trump-s-friend-repeats-assertion-that-president-may-fire-mueller |title=Trump Has No Plans to Fire Special Counsel, Spokeswoman Says |date=June 13, 2017 |publisher=[[Bloomberg LP]]|last1=Olorunnipa|first1=Toluse|last2=Edgerton|first2=Anna|last3=Dopp|first3=Terrence}}</ref> * '''June 14''': ''The Washington Post'' confirms that Mueller is investigating Trump for [[obstruction of justice]], in relation to his dismissal of Comey.<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/world/national-security/special-counsel-is-investigating-trump-for-possible-obstruction-of-justice/2017/06/14/9ce02506-5131-11e7-b064-828ba60fbb98_story.html |title=Special counsel is investigating Trump for possible obstruction of justice, officials say |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |date=June 14, 2017 |access-date=June 15, 2017|last1=Barrett|first1=Devlin|last2=Entous|first2=Adam|last3=Nakashima|first3=Ellen|last4=Horwitz|first4=Sari}}</ref> * '''June 16''': Trump tweets: "I am being investigated for firing the FBI Director by the man who told me to fire the FBI Director! Witch Hunt."<ref name="Twitter_Trump_6/7/2017">{{cite tweet|authorlink=Donald Trump |last=Trump |first=Donald J.|title=I am being investigated for firing the FBI Director by the man who told me to fire the FBI Director! Witch Hunt. |user=realDonaldTrump |date=June 7, 2017 |number=875701471999864833 | access-date=June 18, 2017}}</ref> * '''June 18''': Trump's lawyer [[Jay Sekulow]] states that he has not been notified of any investigation into Trump himself.<ref>{{cite interview |last=Sekulow |first=Jay |author-link=Jay Sekulow |interviewer=[[John Dickerson (journalist)|John Dickerson]] |title=Transcript: Jay Sekulow on "Face the Nation," June 18, 2017 |work=[[Face the Nation]] |publisher=[[CBS News]] |date=June 18, 2017 |url=http://www.cbsnews.com/news/transcript-jay-sekulow-on-face-the-nation-june-18-2017/ |access-date=June 19, 2017 |quote=SEKULOW: The president is not and has not been under investigation.<br>DICKERSON: How do you know?<br>SEKULOW: Because we've received no notice of investigation. There has been no notification from the special counsel's office that the president is under investigation.}}</ref> * '''June 19''': ABC News contradicts the ''Post''{{'}}s report of June 14, saying no decision has yet been made on whether to investigate Trump for potential obstruction of justice.<ref name="thomas17">{{cite news |last=Thomas |first=Pierre |date=June 19, 2017 |title=Where Things Stand with special counsel Mueller’s Russia Probe |url= http://abcnews.go.com/Politics/things-stand-special-counsel-muellers-russia-probe/story?id=48142304 |publisher=[[ABC News]] |quote=According to sources familiar with the process ... [a]n assessment of evidence and circumstances will be completed before a final decision is made to launch an investigation of the president of the United States regarding potential obstruction of justice.}}</ref> * '''June 20''' ** Speaking about her campaign and party in a ''Politico'' interview, Jill Stein says, "I am certainly not aware of any ties whatsoever, financial or otherwise, to the Russian government."<ref name=politico-20170620>{{cite news |url=https://www.politico.com/magazine/story/2017/06/20/jill-stein-green-party-no-regrets-2016-215281 |title=Jill Stein Isn't Sorry |date=June 20, 2017 |work=[[Politico]]|last=Schrenkinger|first=Ben}}</ref> ** [[Ukrainian President]] [[Petro Poroshenko]] meets with Trump at the [[White House]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Trump calls Otto Warmbier’s death ‘a total disgrace,’ indirectly blames Obama’s inaction|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/news/post-politics/wp/2017/06/20/trump-calls-otto-warmbiers-death-a-total-disgrace-indirectly-blames-obamas-inaction/|website=[[The Washington Post]]|date=June 20, 2017|access-date=May 23, 2018|last=Rucker|first=Philip|author-link=Philip Rucker}}</ref> The [[Government of Ukraine|Ukrainian Government]] paid [[Michael Cohen (lawyer)|Michael Cohen]] between $400,000 and $600,000 to arrange the meeting. A week after Poroshenko returns to [[Kiev]], the [[National Anti-Corruption Bureau of Ukraine]] stops investigating [[Paul Manafort|Manafort]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Trump lawyer 'paid by Ukraine' to arrange White House talks|url=https://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-44215656|website=BBC News|da